definitions.definition: A river in southern England , flowing 336 km (209 mi. ) from Gloucestershire , through Wiltshire , Oxfordshire , Berkshire , Buckinghamshire , Surrey and Greater London , and between Essex and Kent to the Thames Estuary and North Sea .
A sea area centred on the Thames Estuary .
A river in Ontario , Canada , flowing 258 km (160 mi. ) to Lake St. Clair .
A river in the U.S. State of Connecticut flowing 24 km (15 mi. ) past New London to Long Island Sound .
A town in Waikato , New Zealand , situated on the Firth of Thames (a large bay) and the Coromandel Peninsula.
